cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with sequence to sequence models and their ability to conduct a compositional task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the architecture and training of neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper analyzes the structural differences between the two model types, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses a lookup table task, which could be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
